---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Hawaiʻi Growing — Cannabis Cultivation on Oahu"
  description="Oahu-specific cannabis cultivation guides. 329 homegrow education, outdoor growing, climate challenges, pest pressure, and field notes from an active Hawaii garden."
>

  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="breadcrumb">Hawaii Growing</div>
      <h1>Growing Cannabis<br /><em>In Hawaiʻi</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Oahu-specific growing conditions, climate challenges, and 329 education.</p>
      <div class="meta-row">
        <span class="meta-tag">329</span>
        <span class="meta-tag">Outdoor</span>
        <span class="meta-tag">Climate</span>
        <span class="meta-tag">IPM</span>
        <span class="meta-tag">Oahu</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hibiscus-divider">✿ &nbsp; ✿ &nbsp; ✿</div>

  <div class="silo-index">
    <p class="lead">Hawaii cannabis cultivation comes with challenges most mainland guides never address — persistent humidity, year-round pest pressure, compressed light cycles, salt air, and a legal framework unique to the state. These pages document what I've learned growing here.</p>

    <div class="article-list">

      <a href="/hawaii-growing/329-homegrow-hawaii" class="article-card">
        <div class="article-card-label">329 · Legal</div>
        <h2>329 Homegrow Hawaiʻi</h2>
        <p>What medical patients can actually grow. Plant counts, tagging requirements, caregiver rules, possession limits, and the 2028 sunset to know about.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/hawaii-growing/growing-cannabis-hawaii" class="article-card">
        <div class="article-card-label">Overview</div>
        <h2>Growing Cannabis in Hawaiʻi</h2>
        <p>What's different about cultivating cannabis in Hawaii. Indoor vs outdoor, climate basics, growing systems, water quality, and light cycle considerations.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/hawaii-growing/outdoor-cannabis-hawaii" class="article-card">
        <div class="article-card-label">Outdoor</div>
        <h2>Outdoor Cannabis Hawaiʻi</h2>
        <p>Location selection, timing, genetics, soil, watering, IPM, and staying compliant with 329 outdoors. What actually works here.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/hawaii-growing/hawaii-cannabis-climate" class="article-card">
        <div class="article-card-label">Climate</div>
        <h2>Hawaiʻi Cannabis Climate Challenges</h2>
        <p>Humidity, temperature, wind, rainfall by region, UV intensity, and salt air. What the guides don't tell you about growing in Hawaii.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/hawaii-growing/cannabis-pest-pressure-hawaii" class="article-card">
        <div class="article-card-label">IPM</div>
        <h2>Cannabis Pest Pressure in Hawaiʻi</h2>
        <p>Year-round IPM in a climate that never resets. Thrips, russet mites, fungus gnats, caterpillars, botrytis — and the system that stays ahead of it.</p>
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .silo-index {
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 2rem 5rem;
  }

  .article-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .article-card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--gold);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
    background: var(--cream);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .article-card:hover {
    background: #ede8dd;
  }

  .article-card-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .article-card h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .article-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }
</style>
